The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 September is 76,274 (8,791 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 September, there were 2,223 new confirmed cases (256.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 September, there were 1,486 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 50% (737 extra cases).
